destination device

post.description:
**ZDO_NWK_ADDR_REQ**

This message will request the device to send a â€œNetwork Address Requestâ€. This message sends a
broadcast message looking for a 16 bit address with a known 64 bit IEEE address. You must
subscribe to â€œZDO Network Address Responseâ€ to receive the response to this message. Check
section 3.0.1.7 for more details on callback subscription. The response message listed below only
indicates whether or not the message was received properly.

200.description: Status is either Success (0) or Failure (1).

requestBody.description:
ieeeaddr => 64 bit IEEE address of the device

reqtype => (0 Single Device response) or  (1 Extended, include associated devices) 

startindex  => Starting index into the list of children. This is used to get more of the list if the list is too large for one message

post.description:
**ZDO_IEEE_ADDR_REQ**

This command will request a deviceâ€™s IEEE 64-bit address. You must subscribe to â€œZDO IEEE
Address Responseâ€ to receive the data response to this message. The response message listed
below only indicates whether or not the message was received properly

200.description: Status is either Success (0) or Failure (1).

reqtype => (0 Single Device response) or  (1 Extended, include associated devices)

post.summary: Bind and un-bind device and group
post.description:
**ZDO_BIND_REQ**

This command is generated to request a Bind.

**ZDO_UNBIND_REQ (required dstaddr & nwkaddrofinterest)**

This command is generated to request an un-bind.

200.description: Status is either Success (0) or Failure (1).

requestBody.description:
dstaddr => NWK address of the device generating the bind request

srcaddr => 64 bit IEEE address of the device generating the bind request

srcendpoint => Specifies the binding source endpoint.

clusterid => Specifies the cluster Id to match in messages.

(genOnOff 6 / genLevelCtrl 8) 

view https://github.com/zigbeer/zcl-id/wiki#Table

dstaddrmode => Specifies destination address mode

(0 address not present / 1 group address / 2 address 16 bits /3 address 64 bits / 255 broadcast)

addr_short_long => Binding destination IEEE address. Not to be confused with DstAddr.

dstendpoint => Specifies the binding destination endpoint. It is used only when DstAddrMode is 64 bits extended address

**example bind 0x000d6ffffe270288 to group 10 :**
  dstaddr: 11072
  srcaddr: '0x000d6ffffe270288'
  srcendpoint: 1
  clusterid: 6
  dstaddrmode: 2
  addr_short_long: '0x000000000000000a'
  dstendpoint: 1

**example bind coordinator 0x00124b0018ecde4f to device  0x000d6ffffe270288:** 
  dstaddr: 0
  srcaddr: '0x00124b0018ecde4f'
  srcendpoint: 1
  clusterid: 6
  dstaddrmode: 3
  addr_short_long: '0x000d6ffffe270288'
  dstendpoint: 1
